The paper deals with secure communication and proposes a novel two-phase communication scheme that involves the use of artificial noise to achieve secrecy capacity. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of artificial noise in wireless communication, which is a topic in networked systems (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed scheme involves the use of a full-duplex transmitter, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
